---
import Section from './Section.astro'

const failures = [
  {
    title: 'they redo each other’s work',
    body: 'agent B re-reads every file agent A just read — same greps, same conclusions, tokens burned twice.',
  },
  {
    title: 'they forget everything',
    body: 'tomorrow’s run re-derives today’s context from zero. a cold worker opened 9 files where a warm one needed 1.',
  },
  {
    title: 'their notes don’t connect',
    body: 'two findings about the same module sit as unrelated blobs — nothing links SessionToken to the login flow.',
  },
]
---

<Section id="problem" title="run one agent and it's easy. run a fleet and you've quietly built a small distributed system.">
  <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
    {failures.map((f) => (
      <div class="rounded-md border border-lp-border bg-lp-surface p-5">
        <h3 class="font-mono text-sm text-lp-fg">▸ {f.title}</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-lp-muted">{f.body}</p>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>
  <p class="mt-8 max-w-2xl text-pretty text-lp-muted">
    and the usual fix makes it worse: you gave each agent its own worktree — and quietly deleted
    the shared state everyone was leaning on.
  </p>
</Section>
